originalText.text: I have always admired Safe Horizon. I was an intern at Sanctuary for Families back in 2005/2006 and often referred survivors of domestic violence to Safe Horizon. I was very impressed with the services that were provided. In 2018, I was referred to Safe Horizon for crisis counseling as a victim of trauma. My first counselor was helpful but wasn't exactly the best fit for me. I was referred to someone else who accepted my insurance but never followed through. No phone call to schedule an appointment, never returned my phone calls which in my opinion is very unprofessional. I ended going elsewhere for therapy. I still recommend Safe Horizon overall. I just had a bad experience.
